description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;INTERNAL ONLY TO NORTH CUMBRIA INTEGRATED CARE NHS FOUNDATION TRUST (NCIC) TRUST EMPLOYEES ONLY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;25 hours per week, part time, office hrs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Quality &amp; Nursing Directorate, led by the Executive Chief Nurse, supports all areas within North Cumbria Integrated Care NHS Foundation Trust (NCIC) to deliver well governed, quality, safe services. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic and motivated individual to join the Risk Management team in the key role of System Officer. The post holder will provide essential support on the Trust’s incident and risk management systems and processes to enable their effective utilisation by frontline staff across the organisation. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;They will support the development of the Trusts Ulysses system for recording incidents, CAS alerts, risks and other modules. Provide Performance Reports to meet the needs of the Trust Board, Executive Management Team, Care Groups, Committees and Boards, and others as requested or as defined by the Information Analyst Manager. Liaise with all Care Groups in delivering their requirements related to governance information. Undertake analytical work on a scheduled, and where necessary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In addition the role involves working with colleagues to ensure quality of data within the system is of a high standard, and a key member of the in-house expert team for the system dealing with queries and helping to ensure patient safety information is collected and effectively used. This is therefore an ideal opportunity for someone with an interest in risk management and patient safety to support the delivery of quality care to our patients. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews will be held, via Microsoft teams, provisionally on Friday 20th November 2020. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you would like to know more about this opportunity please contact Mike Stacey (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Mike.Stacey@ncic.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;)&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt; Or &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Maureen Gordon (07920086460 / &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Maureen.Gordon@ncic.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please ensure that you document evidence of meeting all the essential criteria in the supporting information.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;If sufficient response is received this post could be closed earlier than the specified closing date, please apply as soon as possible to ensure that your application is considered.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust is committed to safeguarding adults and children therefore if the post is subject to the Rehabilitation of Offenders Act (ROA) 1974 (Exceptions) Order 1975 (as amended) the successful candidate(s) will be subject to a criminal records check with the Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS). The cost of the DBS must be met by the successful candidate(s) through salary deduction. DBS charges are as follows &lt;strong&gt;if applicable to the post:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Standard Check: £26 + Administration cost of £4.20 = deducted at £10.20 from 1st month salary and £10 deducted from salary over following 2 months.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Enhanced Check: £44 + administration cost of £4.20 = £15.20 deducted from 1st month salary and £11 deducted from salary over following 3 months.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As part of the one of the largest employers in the UK NCIC future employees will have also access to the following benefits.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A lease car may be available for this position; further details will be provided upon appointment if applicable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;27 day holiday scheme rising to 33 after 10 years &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Flexible working Scheme &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Excellent opportunities for development &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Competitive NHS Pension scheme&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Access to NHS discounts with retailers and leisure companies&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;EAP (Employee Assistance Programme) a free, confidential counselling and information service to assist with personal or work-related problems&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;These schemes are subject to availability&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
